            <title>[LU-13950] Do not crash if lnet_sock_getaddr returns error</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13950</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some issues with a network lead to panic in the ksocknal_accept&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
rc = lnet_sock_getaddr(sock, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;, &amp;amp;peer_ip, &amp;amp;peer_port);
LASSERT(rc == 0); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* we succeeded before */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s pass this error to the caller.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
